SELENA - Simple Virtual Assistant

SAV is a very simple application implementing tooltips as a virtual assistant.
Requires jQuery, jQuery cookie plugin and Twitter Bootstrap (all included).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Running Selena

<script type="text/javascript" src="js/jquery.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript" src="js/jquery.cookie.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript" src="js/svassistant.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript" src="bootstrap/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>

<script>
    $(document).ready( function() {
	Selena.SelenaRun();
    });
</script>

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. Hide Selena's modal window

$('.sva-hidder').click( function()

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Show Selena's modal window:

$('.sva-enabler i').click( function()

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. Change Selena's text:

$('.response').html( "response text here..." );

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5. changing Selena's response text:

<div class="sva-[class name]">hoover me!</div>

where: [class name] - corresponding to <id> element in .xml file with Selena's phrases:

-- sample.xml --
<items>
    <item>
	<id>sample01</id>
	<text>This is sample solution for Your problem number 1</text>
    </item>
    <item>
	<id>sample02</id>
	<text>This is my proposition for problem number 2 :)</text>
    </item>
</items>


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6. Selena's modal windows:

    a) full-size:

	<!--
 
	    Selena visible modal window
	
	-->	
	<div class="modal sva-modal"  style="display: none">
	     <div class="modal-header">
		<i class="sva-hidder btn btn-small"><a class="icon-arrow-up" title="hide Assistant"></a></i>
	    </div>
	    <div class="modal-body">
		<div class="img-container">
		    <img src="assistant/assistant.jpg" />
		</div>
		<div class="well response">
		    Hello, my name is Selena, and I'm Your Virtual Assistant :)
		</div>
	    </div>
	    <div class="modal-footer">
		<a class="footer-text">
		    <span>S</span>imple
		    <span>V</span>irtual
		    <span>A</span>ssistant &copy;2012 | bl4de
		</a>
	    </div>
	</div>
	<!--assistant modal window-->


    b) hidden:


	<!-- 

	    Selena permanent hiden modal window - shows only on 'mouseover' events

	-->
	<div class="modal sva-minimized" style="display: none">
	    <div class="modal-body">
		<div class="img-container">
		    <img src="assistant/assistant.jpg" />
		</div>
		<div class="well response">
		    Hello, my name is Selena, and I'm Your Virtual Assistant :)
		</div>
	    </div>
	</div>
	<!-- permanent hiden assistant modal window - shows only on mouseover-->

